I"‚<p>This feature makes it possible for you to manage the fields in Ad forms when a user publishes a new ad, by turning them ON/OFF.</p>

<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>

<ol>
  <li>Go to the Panel, <strong>Settings</strong> -&gt; <strong>Advertisement</strong> -&gt; <strong>Advertisement Fields</strong></li>
  <li>Scroll down until you find the <em>Advertisement Fields</em> section.</li>
</ol>

<p><a href="//docs.yclas.com/images/advertisement-fields.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//docs.yclas.com/images/advertisement-fields.png" alt="AdvertisementFields" />
</a></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Address:</strong> Displays the field Address in the Ad form.</li>
  <li><strong>Phone:</strong> Displays the field Phone in the Ad form.</li>
  <li><strong>Website:</strong> Displays the field Website in the Ad form.</li>
  <li><strong>Location:</strong> Displays the field Select Location in the Ad form.</li>
  <li><strong>Price:</strong> Displays the field Price in the Ad form.</li>
  <li><strong>Upload File:</strong> Displays the field File in the Contact form when someone contacts a user for an ad.</li>
  <li><strong>Number of Images:</strong> The maximum number of images a user can upload when publishing an ad.</li>
</ul>

<p><br /></p>

